      • find

        public E find(E elem)
        Given an element, returns the representative element of the set containing that element. If the element is not contained in the structure, this method throws a NoSuchElementException.
        Parameters:
        elem - The element to look up.
        Returns:
        The representative of the set containing the element.
        Throws:

      • union

        public void union(E one,
                  E two)
        Given two elements, unions together the sets containing those elements. If either element is not contained in the set, throws a NoSuchElementException.
        Parameters:
        one - The first element to link.
        two - The second element to link.
        Throws:
        java.util.NoSuchElementException - If either element does not exist.
